# Run the project Locally

In this lecture we will use the `docker compose` which is installed as part of `docker`.

Just go to the directory of cloned repo and run `docker compose up`.

Video of the lecture is self explanatory.

git clone url
cd name
docker compose up
increase the volume from 8 gb to 30 gb for the instance

lsblk
sudo apt install cloud-guest-utils
# here we are selecting /dev/xvda1 because its in /(root directory mounted, which we want to mounted is also on /dev/xvda1)
sudo growpart /dev/xvda 1
lsblk
sudo resize2fs /dev/xvda1
df -h
docker compose up -d
